## Infrastructure-Level Protection

Don't rely solely on application-level defences. Your infrastructure should provide additional layers:

### Use a Web Application Firewall (WAF)

Services like Cloudflare, AWS WAF, or Fastly provide:

- DDoS protection
- Managed rulesets for common attack patterns
- Geoblocking when appropriate
- Automatic bot detection

Yes, these cost money. They're worth it. A single successful attack will cost more than years of WAF fees.

### Implement Challenge-Response for Suspicious Traffic

Rather than blocking suspicious requests outright, challenge them:

- Serve a JavaScript challenge that bots can't easily solve
- Require proof-of-work for high-risk actions
- Use progressive challenges that escalate with suspicion level

